# binary-analyzer

A static analysis tool for executable files. Extracts reverse-engineering indicators — file type, architecture, imported functions, strings, Shannon entropy, and risk scoring — from PE (Windows) and ELF (Linux) binaries. Includes a full quarantine workflow for suspicious file isolation and review.

