## Running Tests

Install dev dependencies and run the full suite from the repo root:

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"
python -m pytest tests/ -q
```

Expected output:

```
27 passed in 0.5s
```

Test files:

| File | Coverage |
|---|---|
| `tests/test_risk.py` | Risk classification, rank ordering, minimum checks |
| `tests/test_analysis.py` | File type detection, `build_results` end-to-end |
| `tests/test_cli.py` | Isolation trigger logic |
| `tests/test_quarantine.py` | Manifest parsing, CSV export |
| `tests/test_rules.py` | Rules loading, merging, validation, env/CLI resolution |

