## CLI Reference

```
usage: python -m binary_analyzer [-h] [--json] [--max-strings N] [--rules PATH]
                                  [--auto-isolate] [--isolate-threshold N]
                                  [--isolate-on-risk {LOW,MEDIUM,HIGH}]
                                  [--keyword-isolate-threshold N]
                                  [--quarantine-dir DIR]
                                  [--list-quarantine]
                                  [--restore SHA256_PREFIX]
                                  [--delete-from-quarantine SHA256_PREFIX]
                                  [--export-manifest-csv [PATH]]
                                  [binary_file]
```

| Argument | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `binary_file` | — | Path to the file to analyze |
| `--json` | off | Output machine-readable JSON |
| `--max-strings N` | 10 | Number of strings to include in preview |
| `--rules PATH` | — | JSON rules file (merged with defaults) |
| `--auto-isolate` | off | Move suspicious files to quarantine |
| `--isolate-threshold N` | 25 | Isolate when suspicion score >= N |
| `--isolate-on-risk LEVEL` | — | Also isolate when risk >= LEVEL |
| `--keyword-isolate-threshold N` | 0 | Also isolate when string hits >= N (0 = off) |
| `--quarantine-dir DIR` | `quarantine` | Quarantine directory |
| `--list-quarantine` | — | List files currently in quarantine |
| `--restore PREFIX` | — | Restore file by SHA-256 prefix |
| `--delete-from-quarantine PREFIX` | — | Permanently delete by SHA-256 prefix |
| `--export-manifest-csv [PATH]` | — | Export manifest.jsonl to CSV |

